Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4). Dice @tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, tomato, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @vegan chipotle mayonnaise{4%tbsp} with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Veggies ==

Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, sliced onion, and half the @Southwest spice blend{1/2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer to a plate. Reserve pan.

== Beans ==

Heat same #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, remaining Southwest spice blend, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat; gently mash beans with a #potato masher{} or back of a #spoon{}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. (TIP: If mixture is too thick, stir in a splash of water.) Season with salt and pepper.

== Tortillas ==

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with @olive oil{1%tbsp}; brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer (divide between 2 sheets for 4). Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}.

Bake on top rack, flipping halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. (For 4, bake on top and middle racks; flipping tortillas and swapping rack positions halfway through.) TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

== Assembly ==

Once tortillas are toasted, remove sheet from oven. Carefully spread each tortilla with smashed beans, then top with veggies and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Return to top rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide tostadas between plates. Top with pico de gallo, vegan chipotle lime sauce, and remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.